{
  "stem": "21482.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think my mother had some money, my parent must have had some money.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I actually remember that they had some dollars, some gold dollars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she must have been selling it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were buying, you know, what we would eat in the ghetto, what was the biggest food, was we would have bread and we would have potatoes.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I don't even-- don't think we had any milk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember having any milk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I certainly don't remember having any meat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe in the beginning, I think, when my father was still working, you know, in the beginning of the ghetto, when he was still going out to the store.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But once he couldn't go out anymore-- most people couldn't go out, except those people that work for Oskar Schindler, for Madritsch, and for Optima.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those were factories that people would go and work and were able to have contact with Polish workers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And those people were able to buy some food and smuggle it into the ghetto for their families.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the rest of the people had very little.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I really didn't know any people, because when people went to work for Oskar Schindler in the beginning, a lot of people did not want to go and work for a factory outside of the ghetto because they were afraid that they would leave in the morning, they would come back at night, their families would be arrested, they would be taken out of the ghetto on trucks.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people were afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But within a very short time, most families had broken up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most mothers were taken away, fathers were taken away, children were taken away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if the parents were taken away, there were so many orphans.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
